Preheat your #oven{} to 220 degrees. Remove the core from the @red pepper{1} and
@yellow pepper{1/2} and chop into bite-sized chunks. Toss the peppers in a splash
of @olive oil{a splash}, place on a lined #baking tray{} and cook on the top shelf
of your oven for ~{15%mins}.

> The peppers are ready when slightly crispy at the edges - keep an eye on them.

In a #pot{}, boil the @water{275%ml} with the @vegetable stock pot{1/2}. Add the
@buckwheat{150%g}. Gently boil until the top of the buckwheat starts to come out
of the water, then place a #lid{} on the pot. Leave on the lowest heat for
~{10%mins} before removing (don't touch the lid until serving).

Peel and finely chop the @red onion{1/2}(peeled and finely chopped) and
@garlic clove{2}(finely chopped). Finely chop the @green chilli{1/2}(finely chopped).
Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}(grated). Roughly chop the @chives{1/2}(roughly chopped).

Heat a splash of @olive oil{a splash} in a #non-stick frying pan{} on medium
heat. Once hot, add in your red onion, garlic and chilli.

> The chilli is a bit cheeky so add less if you don't want too much heat.

Cook for around ~{5%mins} until soft (but not coloured).

Add the @ground cumin{1/2%tsp}, @mild paprika{1/2%tsp} and @ground cinnamon{1/2%tsp}
and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

> If you're not a huge fan of cinnamon, just add half!

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%400g can} before tipping into the pan. Stir
together with a @salt{pinch} and a few grinds of @black pepper{}. Cook for another
~{1%minute} and then remove from the heat until your buckwheat is ready.

Once your buckwheat is done (it should be dry not soggy), fluff it up with a #fork{}
to separate the grains and then stir into your black bean mixture, together with
your peppers. Stir through half the @crème fraîche{1}(half), test for seasoning
and add more salt if necessary.

Tip your black bean mixture into an #ovenproof dish{} and top with your cheese.
Place on the highest shelf of your oven until the top is beautifully golden and
crisp.

Serve with a big dollop of crème fraîche, a scattering of chives and a big
welcoming smile!